\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 14. T. asiaticum} L.,{\i  Mantissa} 80 (1767). Dwarf shrub with annual flowering stems c. 40 cm. Leaves up to 30 mm, narrowly oblong, dentate, gradually attenuate at base, acute, glandular and sparsely puberulent, shortly petiolate. Inflorescence very lax; lower bracts leaf-like and much longer than the flowers; upper bracts short. Calyx glandular but almost glabrous; teeth c. ½ as long as tube, broadly ovate, aristate. Corolla 10-13 mm, pink to purple.{\i  Shady rocks. • Islas Baleares.} Bl.
